# Emotional World Interface System

Before UI, scene, or visual implementation, read:

`docs/KWALIFY_FINAL_UI_BLUEPRINT.md` (canonical) · `docs/KWALIFY_EMOTIONAL_WORLD_UI_SPEC.md`

Product promise still governed by `docs/KWALIFY_CREATIVE_NORTH_STAR.md` (playlist primary).

Hard rules:
- One screen = one emotion = one hero object = one controlled environment
- Geometric / semi-geometric shapes only; no blobs, watercolor, or cluttered scenes
- 2.5D layers: hero → ambient hints → gradient field
- Single soft light; edge glow on hero only
- Silhouette readable in 1 second; hero grounded (shadow/glow)
- Home: emotion nodes with mini vignettes; hover lift + glow; click zoom into world (0.6–1.2s), not hard cuts
- Search: emotion interpretations, not keyword results
- One geometric sans; controlled saturation per scene

If output looks like AI slop (amorphous shapes, HDR, multiple focal points), stop and replace with a clean geometric hero.

Still art: `docs/KWALIFY_VISUAL_STYLE_TLDR.md` and Phase 1 Figma checklist for fuel pump.
